The paper focuses on uncertainty estimation in machine learning models, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The specific application of the model is in detecting atrial fibrillation from ECG signals, which falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of ECG signals also suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the improvement of the algorithm's performance, which could be relevant to the subfield of signal processing (cs.SI).
